run(sql="

with cte as(
    select * from(
        select TO_DATE(FROM_UNIXTIME(timestamp/1000)) as date, sessionId, orderId, utmContent, row_number() over(partition by orderId order by timestamp) as rn 
        from `last15Days(orderSuccessView)`     
    ) 
    where rn=1
),

cte2 as(
select * from(
    select TO_DATE(FROM_UNIXTIME(timestamp/1000)) as date, guid, sessionId, utmContent, utmSource, utmCampaign 
    from `last15Days(appLaunch)` 
    where TO_DATE(FROM_UNIXTIME(timestamp/1000))>='2023-03-20'
    union 
    select TO_DATE(FROM_UNIXTIME(startTime/1000)) as date, firstGuid as guid, sessionId, utmContent, utmSource, utmCampaign 
    from `last15Days(sessionSummary)` 
    where TO_DATE(FROM_UNIXTIME(startTime/1000))>='2023-03-20'
) order by guid
)

select date, count(distinct orderId) as SS_Orders 
from(
    select cte.date, cte.sessionId, cte.orderId, cte2.utmContent, pv.pogId, dp.categoryName
    from cte2 left join cte 
    on cte.sessionId=cte2.sessionId
    left join `last15Days(productView)` pv
    on cte2.sessionId=pv.sessionId
    left join `all(dProduct)` dp
    on pv.pogId=dp.pogId
    where lower(cte2.utmContent) like '%dpanew%' and dp.categoryName='Sexual Wellness'
    )
group by date 
order by date desc

",1000)

run(sql="

with cte as(
    select * from(
        select TO_DATE(FROM_UNIXTIME(timestamp/1000)) as date, sessionId, orderId, utmContent, row_number() over(partition by orderId order by timestamp) as rn 
        from `last15Days(orderSuccessView)`     
    ) 
    where rn=1
)

select date, count(distinct orderId) as Orders 
from (
select a.date, a.orderId, a.sessionId, b.pogId, c.categoryName from cte a
left join `last15Days(productView)` b
on a.sessionId=b.sessionId
left join `all(dProduct)` c
on b.pogId=c.pogId
)
where categoryName = 'Sexual Wellness'
group by date 
order by date desc
",1000)
